 NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/urewena.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rewena</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>RTA WebAdmin</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>posts: </FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>126</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFF00>12/19/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFF00>10:13:05 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><img src=http://boh.thixo.net/artwork/board_art/rewena.jpg width=58 height=74></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B>&nbsp;<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Doledar, RoS and the incident... cont</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">I called in the BB guild that night in fear.<br>
<br>
I was concerned about Post Mortem, they are one of the last few raids transfered from the old calendar. They had problems and violations in their hate raid a few weeks ago. When I found out Zippiy(the gm) had logged and that they were giving up on the raid and leaving the plane fully popped including Cazic I contacted Mistabone in bots and Nanaliya (please forgive any spelling errors) in MFH. I didn't recogise any names of FoR or I would have gone there too.  Unfortunatly both guilds were in the middle of something else. <br>
<br>
Post Mortem does not have posting rights on the new calendar, this was their last raid.<br>
<br>
This situation was being discussed in other places, Dole I hope you have the support of your guild for bringing it public.<br>
<br>
There are problems with the Big brother system the way it is now. <br>
<br>
NO ONE IS TO BLAME <br>
<br>
It just isn't working the way we ALL thought it would. The admins were afraid that too much critisism straight out like this might bring about the fall of the whole calendar.<br>
<br>
What would be nice at this point in time is some CONSTUCTIVE ideas on how the problems can be fixed, and perhaps the problems themselves to be identified.<br>
<br>
From my perspective there are two problems:<br>
<br>
One the BB guilds are not taking turns, no notice of which guild is up is anywhere.<br>
<br>
Two they get informed too late, and either can't do it or the god raid goes too late thus affecting the next day's raid.<br>
<br>
BOTS, KEG, and CIW have all been in fear too late. It is not a single guild at fault, again I blame the system.<br>
<br>
I think in defense of the BB guilds they have followed their end, not zoning in before asked, and letting the guild of day (so to speak) try the god first. The system as it is just will not work. <br>
<br>
Lets fix it and not throw mud =)<br>
<br>
One idea I had is perhaps each bb guild take a week for a specific plane. In this way it can be posted in advance, that way the BB knows ahead of time that it is &quot;ON CALL&quot; maybe leave a cleric logged in there for the week etc etc. The other guilds know exactly who to call. <br>
<br>
Any other ideas?</font><P><i><b>Rewena Bloodstorm</b></i>
