</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#000000><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ubiasschmias.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bias Schmias</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Tad-pole</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>posts: </FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>91</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFF00>12/19/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFF00>11:11:30 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B>&nbsp;<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Suggestions</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial"><br>
My .02:<br>
<br>
I would suggest the following for calling in a BB guild.  These may be things people don't like from the non-BB side, but this is probably the best way to ensure the bigbrother call-up doesn't overrun the next day's raid.<br>
<br>
Uno) Cutoff time for calling up the BB guild.  Say 11pm PST.  If at 11pm PST you know the god isn't going down, you bring on the BB.  This ensures the bigbrother portion of the raid doesn't overlap (much) with the next day's time.<br>
<br>
dos) Rewena's idea of Big Brother guilds being 'on call' for a stretch of days is a good one, and should be implemented.  requires the least amount of work for the near future.  Ideally, the raid leader goes to the calendar, sees who is next on the list, and uses their admin/posting privs to indicate they brought up big brother, and cause the list to rotate to the next person.<br>
<br>
tres) Confirm &amp; Establish in extremely clear language the rules for epic looting planes.  Make it explicit (use RFC language conventions MUST/SHOULD/WILL NOT/etc) that big brother guilds go up and get nothing but epic quest items, and make a list of what those items are.  For example, the magician staff that Inny (is it inny?) drops.  It's for an epic quest, but it's also a staff that any magician would want to have.  Does it count as epic loot?  I would guess yes, but it's not very clear.  We all know what the list of epic stuff is, so that should be put up on a list on the Big Brother page so we all (BB &amp; others) know what the items are that may be looted.<br>
<br>
cuatro) Integrate the BB calendar system with the existing calendar display.  Until we can come up with an acceptable way to round-robin the big brother guilds, I suspect a weekly 'rotation' (or every 3 or 4 days, whatever it takes to get them all on the rotation in a month) is the best solution, since it allows everyone to schedule.<br>
<br>
cinco) This is not meant as a slam at anyone in particular, but: People need to be goddamn well respectful when they're up there.  Both BB &amp; the raiding group.  If you're in the raid and someone starts slagging on the members of CIW for coming up to kill the god, shut 'em up or shut 'em down.  If your guild is going up as a Big Brother and people start acting rude, port them out of the plane.  We all have to get along to a lesser or greater degree, and EVERYONE gets frayed nerves in a plane after 12 hours.  Without respect on both sides, the Big Brother assistance will just cause more problems than it'll solve.<br>
<br>
So, to recap my longwinded novel:<br>
<br>
1 - communicate, communicate, communicate.<br>
2 - set up a weekly rotation so everyone knows who is up<br>
3 - require/request communication setup between raiders &amp; BB at start of raid, so BB guild knows if god is up and if they should have a 'team' on standby.<br>
4 - Be respectful, you slobs. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
