<br>
</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#000000><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/umortyeq.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MortyEQ</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Toede Slavedriver</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>posts: </FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>101</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFF00>12/19/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFF00>1:42:04 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B>&nbsp;<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Suggestions</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Actually, the only effect that staying past 2am has on the following day's raid is that mobs killed after 2am will repop later in the day, as long as staying there past 2am does not involve farming repops.  If a god/quest mob is up on the previous day to your raid, you cannot expect it to stay up for your raid.</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#000000><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/usiffu.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Siffu</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.geocities.com/Pipeline/Jump/7614/but.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>RTA Administrator</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>posts: </FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>55</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFF00>12/19/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFF00>1:49:08 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><img src=http://members.home.com/bivan/sif1.jpg height=100 width=150></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B>&nbsp;<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Suggestions</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Okay, here's my recollection of what happened (I have the logs to prove it, but I need to go through them and take out the 'personal' stuff hehe)<br>
<br>
I came on at 2am and heard in guildsay the fact that PM was still in fear and had no intentions of leaving.  Thus the rest of my night was shot negotiating between Tinid Losi, PM, and BoD.  When I got to Fear, it took me a loooong time to finally get PM to leave.  Tindi left a lot earlier, save for Kinwen's alt, who was still dragging corpses.  I have no quarrel with Tindi Losi, they were in communication with me the whole time as to what was going on.<br>
<br>
BoD, through Garrm and Hixx, were also in communication with me as well, and willing to work with us on the issue.  The problem lay in the fact that they were called in much later than they should have, and despite the chagrin of my guild, I made agreed to let BoD have CT and get their epic pieces.  I do wish they would have left when they said they would, but that is understandable after what happened.  They had put a lot of time into getting to CT and pulling the  temple, so I don't blame them.  I would like to say that they actually were very cooperative in this, and tried to honor there BB duties.<br>
<br>
The problem lie in the fact that it was so late.  The agreement reached, the best I could do, was secure the God loot for the rightful owners of the plane date, RoS, and also give BoD the rights to the epic loot.  If it had gone they way it is supposed to go, all guilds, save RoS, should have been gone from the planes at 2am, the cut off.   Vigoe should not have done what he did, and BoD should not have tried to loot CT until AFTER a RoS member got to check the corpse.  This was the arrangement, BoD would get one more chance to kill CT, RoS would loot it, except epic pieces, and then all would go their merry way.  Unfortunately, both sides didn't truly live up to the spirit of the arrangement.  Mind you, RoS does not have need for a BB guild, so they lost out on CT over this, at least the pleasure of killing him and the epic pieces we need for the FA quest, but I guess that's just life, it was more important, to me, to get PM out of there, who shown an unbelieveable level of imcompetence and unwillingness to work with the calendar system, and try and smooth out any tension between BoD and RoS.  I logged before the debacle with Vigoe, but from what I gathered, CT was not dropped until 6am PST, some 4 hours after everyone save RoS, were supposed to be there.  <br>
<br>
I do think there is a problem with the BB system as it effects the guilds not BB, but capable of clearing all of Fear and Hate, but I do not think BoD should be singled out for this.  There were minor slips in the agreement, but I do think they were honorable for the most part.<br>
<br>
As for our side in this issue, I would like to apologize for the loss of the epic pieces.  I do realize that had BoD been called in when they should have been, none of this would have happened.  The only true blame I see here should be on PM's shoulder to bear.  </font><P><html><body>
